A lightweight ircd written in javascript v8 with nodejs.

$Id: README 6 2010-08-18 12:34:37Z mdxico $

Tips:
	1. 	Building up NodeJS:
		Download javascript v8 nodejs project at http://nodejs.org/dist/node-v0.1.98.tar.gz
			./configure
			make 
			make install
		Visit http://nodejs.org/#download for more information.
	
	2. 	IRC clients supported by OpenIRCd: mIRC, X-Chat, KvIRC and irssi.
	
	3.	Default character encoding is utf8.
	
	4.	Setup the config file at config.js (server name, ip binding, port and others)
	
	5.	Run ircd: # node ircd.js
	
